    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Pirating Is Not New</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stephen Lardieri letter holds Europeans who are trying to impose copyright restitution fees on personal computer equipment are overlooking fact that computers were used to pirate software and books long before they were used to pirate music (Feb 14 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Fighting Free Music, Europeans Take Aim at Personal Computers'' (front page, Feb. 14):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Fighting Free Music, Europeans Take Aim at Personal Computers'' (front page, Feb. 14):</p>
        <p>The Europeans who are trying to impose copyright restitution fees on personal computer equipment are overlooking the fact that computers were used to pirate software and books long before they were used to pirate music. The musicians who wish to derive income from such fees need to go to the back of the line: we software developers and authors were here first.</p>
        <p>STEPHEN LARDIERI  Bellevue, Wash., Feb. 14, 2001</p>
      </block>
